  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AMAZE global impact award: increasing school children&apos;s access to CSE through curriculum resources integrated with audio-visual materials</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO will partner with the largest CSE online platform in China, You&amp;Me, to update their existing CSE curriculum with the AMAZE videos that UNESCO has adapted into Chinese, and to organize workshops to train volunteers and school teachers and principals. Through You&amp;Me, the project will engage 10 CSOs from 2 to 3 provinces who will mobilize 200 local volunteers to be trained on CSE delivery. The project will also train teachers and principals from 80 schools of Chongqing municipality. The trained volunteers and teachers will deliver 1500 CSE lessons in 100 schools, serving 50,000 person times. The adapted videos will also be widely disseminated through popular open-learning websites.</narrative>
  </description>
